    <text id="A5516T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 id="d3" type="summary">
                <p>Dold writes to McCue to inquire about a possible teaching position available at
                    Lovingston. This is a letter fragment.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 id="d5" type="letter">
                <opener> Fishersville, Va <dateline>
                        <date value="1860-07-04">July 4th 1860</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Mr. J. H. McCue: <lb/>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Having just recd a letter from Mr. J. Hotchkiss stating that you want a teacher
                    at Lovingston, I therefore drop you a few lines to ascertain what the prospects
                    may be of obtaining the situation.</p>
                <p>I have recently graduated at Emory &amp; Henry College, and can furnish ample
                    references of good moral character &amp;C, not only from the faculty of E.
                    &amp; H. Col. but also from my former teacher. [?] Rev. W. L. Richardson of
                    Waynesboro, Rev. R. [?] Dabney D. D. of Union Seminary, Rev. J. N. Craig, Dr.
                    Walker and others. You will //</p>


            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
